attribute.dc:comment: In the "Information for Building Language Corpora Under German Law" of the DFG Review Board on Linguistics, https://www.dfg.de/download/pdf/foerderung/antragstellung/forschungsdaten/guidelines_review_board_linguistics_corpora.pdf, is explicitly pointed to single rights of the originator and the necessity to obtain these rights. For the question "Which rights have been obtained or what is the status of the rights collection?" this attribute has been added.

Added for the question, if similar research data are already available and why these cannot be used. The DFG Review Board 112 "Economics" and the German Federal Ministry of Education and Research (BMBF) recommend suggestions concerning this question, e.g. "Bereitstellung und Nutzung quantitativer Forschungsdaten in der Bildungsforschung: Memorandum des Fachkollegiums „Erziehungswissenschaft“, https://www.dfg.de/download/pdf/foerderung/antragstellung/forschungsdaten/richtlinien_forschungsdaten_bildungsforschung.pdf
Added for the question which documentation will be available together with the data

Added for the question where the documentation can be found. The DFG Review Board 112 "Economics" expects a meaningful description of the data sets that should be stored either in the journals themselves or in repositories (at universities, research institutes or at central specialized information centers), https://www.dfg.de/download/pdf/foerderung/antragstellung/forschungsdaten/fachkollegium112_forschungsdatenmanagement_de_1811.pdf.

Added for the question which data documention is only available on request. The question may be of relevance for DFG projects in educational research, see Petra Stanat, Bereitstellung und Nutzung quantitativer Forschungsdaten in der Bildungsforschung: Memorandum des Fachkollegiums „Erziehungswissenschaft“ der DFG, https://www.dfg.de/download/pdf/foerderung/antragstellung/forschungsdaten/richtlinien_forschungsdaten_bildungsforschung.pdf

Added for the question "What is the status of the approval process?", recommended in the Manual on handling research data of the DFG review board "Ancient Cultures", i.e. Fachkollegium „Alte Kulturen“, Handreichung zum Umgang mit Forschungsdaten, https://www.dfg.de/download/pdf/foerderung/antragstellung/forschungsdaten/handreichung_fachkollegium_101_forschungsdaten.pdf
